<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-51-0937 </DOCNO><TEXT>Gold mining in the reef gold deposits of Witwatersrand takes place todayat depths varying from the surface (outcrop workings) to more than 3000m below the surface. The deepest air shaft reaches 2400 m; deeper levelsare served via secondary blind shafts. All levels are worked by longwallmining; to keep the member of supporting pillars small, strike lengthsof 500 to 1000 m are being served. A typical underground complement atWitwatersrand is 8000 men. Current underground labour requirements areone employee for approximately 25 t mined per month.</TEXT></DOC>